Approach 2: Character Comparison (Without Creating String)
Intuition

Instead of building the repeated string,

compare each character directly.

Java
class Solution {

    public boolean repeatedSubstringPattern(String s) {

        int n = s.length();

        for (int len = 1; len <= n / 2; len++) {

            if (n % len != 0)
                continue;

            boolean match = true;

            for (int i = len; i < n; i++) {

                if (s.charAt(i) != s.charAt(i % len)) {
                    match = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (match)
                return true;
        }

        return false;
    }
}

