Approach 4: KMP (Prefix / LPS Array) ⭐ Most Optimal
Intuition

If the string is made of repeated substrings,

its Longest Prefix which is also Suffix (LPS) tells us the repeating pattern.

Example

ababab

LPS Array

0 0 1 2 3 4

Last LPS Value

4

Repeating substring length

n - lastLPS

6 - 4 = 2

Since

6 % 2 == 0

Answer is

true
Java (Your Code)
class Solution {

    public boolean repeatedSubstringPattern(String s) {

        int[] prefix = kms(s);

        if (prefix[prefix.length - 1] > 0 &&
            s.length() % (s.length() - prefix[prefix.length - 1]) == 0) {

            return true;

        } else {

            return false;
        }
    }

    public int[] kms(String s) {

        int[] prefix = new int[s.length()];

        int left = 0;
        int right = 1;

        while (right < s.length()) {

            if (s.charAt(left) == s.charAt(right)) {

                prefix[right] = left + 1;

                left++;
                right++;

            } else if (left > 0) {

                left = prefix[left - 1];

            } else {

                right++;
            }
        }

        return prefix;
    }
}

